<font color="#FF0000">AMERICAN HONOR, GLORY &amp; SHAME</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jul 27 12:14:49 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Stop playing the flute doc, let the blind follow the blind. <br>
You fired the first shots and introduced me to Chuck on this thread because his views about AMERICAN pride, honor and glory conflicted with the shame, dishonor, guilt and communistic concepts you spew on this site. <br>
This site is for DIALOG, it does not necessary mean I have to embrace your conscientious objectors view. <br>
The truth doc, I saw you as a traitor nothing less. Like our Vietnam era politicians who swayed in every direction the winds of politics blew. They failed to support the troops they had send to war. That is what lost the war. It was not because we as AMERICA'S fighting men failed to do our job, it was because those entrusted with higher responsibility failed to do theirs. <br>
You mentioned visiting the WALL in little SAIGON, how ironic. I wonder what the Vietnamese would have though of you in their midst. Here they lost everything, their homeland, their homes, relatives, THEIR COUNTRY, because individuals like you who rose in protest against our commitment to fighting Communism in their home land. You tried to convince other to desert; to be draft dodgers, to flee into Canada and when that failed you called them baby killers and murderers. <br><br>
Isn't that what you called me? A murderer? I have never murdered anyone. Do you charge a law enforcement officer with murder for having to take a lifefor having killed the criminal  in the course of his duties? It is not murder in war doc and that's what's wrong with your mind. That's what the protestors shouted and screamed to returning AMERICAN military men who had served their country with honor.  I killed many of the enemies in war and did it because my country called upon me to do so and as an AMERICAN fighting man that was my job, it was my duty. To kill communist soldiers and that is what I did. When we captured them, we treated them as worthy foes but when they shot at us we shot back and did our duty. <br>
There is no shame to that yet, shrinks like you and all those that get paid by government subsidies have for years capitalized upon the pains and suffering YOU INFLICTED at home upon honorable men. <br><br>
We lost the Vietnam War at home. Shrinks like you first get the Vietnam veteran to admit the war was wrong. Then to admit they were pawns in the hands of the government and that what they did was wrong. Once you have accomplished this you' turned an honorable military men who did what his country asked and required of him into another victim of shame and guilt and you are guaranteed another government paycheck. <br>
Who is the murderer here doc?<br>
You and individuals like you murdered AMERICAN pride and honor; you turned it into guilt and shame. You comforted the hurt and misunderstanding of the deserter and cowards who failed to stand up for what was right, you offered him &quot;amnesty&quot; and that was a shame and did a great dishonor to those that died and were wounded in Vietnam. Those who fought against Communist aggression in Vietnam. <br>
The majority of AMERICANS that fought honorably in Vietnam have been pinned down behind rice paddies at home for far too long and so we are beginning to rise above the mud you threw at us.  Our children see a different world then the one you see. They still have faith, hope and trust in America and believe what we did in Vietnam was right. <br><br>
HIDE IN THE BACKROOM DOC? <br><br>
That's what Johnson did. He moved the dialog to Paris, heck we should have said to the communist. We'll going to begin peace talks next week. In the city of Hanoi, with your present government in power or what's left of that city and your government in the parking lot we will make of that city in order to get you to the conference table. <br>
That's what war is doc, that is the way it is played. That is what made our country great. We fought for what we knew was right and did not compromise our principles but you deceived the public and called us baby-killers and murderers to hide your shame and coward hearts.  <br><br>
ONE OF THE STRONGEST AND MOST POWERFUL FORM OF DIALOG AND UNDERSTANDING IS ACHIEVED WHEN THE PUBLIC IS INFORMED.<br>
 <br>
It's accomplished out in the open, not in some back door. Give the AMERICAN public, the visiting Vietnamese, the educator and students of history the opportunity to see both sides of the Vietnam conflict as we saw it in the late 60's and 70's. <br>
Let them make their own decisions as to what happened. Let the AMERICAN public read your fowl responses, which are nothing less then the echoes of what we heard along with the Communistic propaganda YOU SHOUTED AT US when we returned from the war. <br>
Let them judge what we faced on the battle fields and the insults, pain sorrow and shame you inflicted upon honorable men when they returned home to AMERICA. <br>
That's why Vietnam veterans have suffered so much, not because of the war but because when we returned from doing our duty, WE FOUND the likes of you, cowards, traitors and conscientious objectors condemning us for having done our duty. It was you that met us at our front door. <br>
Unfortunately, the majority of Americans remained silent. America's silent majority let it happened, because they did not care enough to get involved. <br><br>
History's shame denied us the right we had to share the victories and the sorrows of war with our loved ones, so we remained silent. <br><br>
Go hide in the backroom you say. Sorry doc but for many of us we have been pinned down in the rice paddies at home for far too long. <br>
As long as I have a CLEAR FIELD OF FIRE, I plan to keep your head down and expose the shame and guilt individuals like you laid upon us. <br><br>
That is what this site is all about, it gives me the opportunity to share with others what I felt and what I did. So that other children of Vietnam veterans can look here and see the pride their father, husbands, spouses felt for having served in the War of Vietnam.<br>
 WHAT DID YOU DO DURING THE WAR DADDY? <br><br>
I am Cook Barela, USMC 1967-1968 I fought in the Vietnam War against Communist soldiers that were trained and armed by the Soviet Union and Communist China and I killed many of them. I am proud of it.<br><br>
If we failed, it was not because we did not do our duty, it was because others entrusted with higher responsibilities failed to do theirs<br><br>

